What is a Stacker Crane?

A Stacker Crane is an automated material handling system designed to transport, store, and retrieve pallets, containers, and goods within Automated Storage and Retrieval Systems (AS/RS). Operating inside narrow warehouse aisles, stacker cranes move both vertically and horizontally to maximize storage density while improving inventory accuracy, warehouse productivity, and operational efficiency.

Modern stacker cranes integrate advanced technologies including:

High-speed Automated Storage & Retrieval Systems (ASRS) for efficient warehouse operations
IoT-enabled Monitoring Systems for real-time equipment diagnostics
AI-powered Predictive Maintenance to reduce downtime and maintenance costs
Smart Warehouse Management System (WMS) Integration for seamless inventory control
Advanced Safety Sensors for collision prevention and operational safety
Energy-efficient Motion Control Systems for sustainable warehouse operations
By automating storage and retrieval processes, stacker cranes help businesses optimize warehouse space, reduce labor costs, improve inventory accuracy, accelerate order fulfillment, and enhance overall supply chain efficiency.

